📖 Instructions: How to Use the OChem Database

🔍 Searching for Chemicals

Type the chemical name or formula in the search bar.

  • A list of suggestions will appear as you type.
  • Click a suggestion to view detailed chemical properties.
  • If a chemical is missing, check spelling or try a different name.

📋 Viewing Chemical Details

Once selected, the chemical's properties will be displayed:

  • Formula - Chemical composition
  • Molecular Weight
  • Melting & Boiling Points
  • Density
  • Hazards & Safety Information

🛒 Adding Chemicals to Cart

To add a chemical to your cart:

  • Click the ➕ button next to the chemical name.
  • The chemical will be stored in your cart, visible at the top-right corner (🛒).
  • Click the cart icon to view or remove items.

📊 Generating a Table

To create a table with selected chemicals:

  • Click "Generate Table" in the navigation bar.
  • A table will automatically generate if your cart contains chemicals.

📥 Downloading the Table

Download your table as a PDF:

  • Click "Download Table as PDF".
  • The file will download as ChemicalTable.pdf.
  • Open the file to view a formatted table.

📢 Requesting a Chemical

If a chemical is missing:

  • Go to the "Request A Chemical" page.
  • Fill in the chemical name and additional details.
  • Click "Submit Request" to send it to the database team.

💡 Tips for Best Experience

  • Use short names or formulas for faster searches.
  • Hover over navbar items to see the highlight effect.
  • Click the cart icon to review selections before generating a table.

🎯 Need Help?

If you encounter issues:

  • Ensure your cart is not empty before generating a table.
  • Check for correct spelling when searching.

Enjoy using OChem Database! 🚀
